Node and Comments Form Settings
http://drupal.org/project/nodeformsettings
==========================================


DESCRIPTION
-----------
This module lets you change several 'small' behaviors with hook_form_alter, in both nodes and comments, doing it per content type so you can configure different aspects of your nodes/comments.


REQUIREMENTS
------------
Drupal 6.x
CCK module (only if you enable CCK Form Settings)

INSTALLING
----------
1. To install the module copy the 'nodeformsettings' folder to your sites/all/modules directory.
2. Go to admin/build/modules. Enable the module(s). Depending on your needs you can activate only one or both modules: "CCK Form Settings", "Node Form Settings", "Comment Form Settings".
Read more about installing modules at http://drupal.org/node/70151

CONFIGURING AND USING - CONTENT TYPES
-------------------------------------
1. Go to admin/content/types
2. Click on the "Edit" link beside the appropriate content type.
3. Scroll down the page. Click on "Node form settings" link.
4. Follow instructions on screen.
5. Click on "Save content type" button.

CONFIGURING AND USING - COMMENTS
--------------------------------
1. Go to admin/content/types

2. Click on the "Edit" link beside the appropriate content type.

3. Scroll down the page. Click on "Comment form settings" link.

4. Follow instructions on screen.

5. Click on "Save content type" button.


CONTRIBUTING. REPORTING ISSUE. REQUESTING SUPPORT. REQUESTING NEW FEATURE.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Go to the module issue queue at http://drupal.org/project/issues/nodeformsettings?status=All&categories=All
2. Click on CREATE A NEW ISSUE link.
3. Fill the form.
4. To get a status report on your request go to http://drupal.org/project/issues/user


UPGRADING
---------
Read more at http://drupal.org/node/250790


